y elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":-140.96,"unit":"% YoY","status":"weak","read":"Profit down 141% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":52.9,"pe_percentile":91.0,"median_pe":39.6,"earnings_yield_pct":1.89,"pb":5.71,"ev_ebitda":20.71,"quality_score":83.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 91-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"Trades at 52.9\u00d7 earnings; multi-year growth not estimable, so 'priced-in' growth is unclear.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[35.0,35.66,35.58,32.18,34.37,36.02,34.41,30.33,29.2,25.56,20.55,20.49],"latest_pct":20.49,"chg_1y_pp":-9.84},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 20